    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 3 for model form requires that the constitutive model and contact formulation be physically motivated and calibrated to material coupon data representative of the implant alloy (Ti-6Al-4V). Bilinear isotropic hardening parameters derived from ASTM E8 tensile tests on bar stock from the same heat as the implant. Frictional contact coefficient validated against separate coupon sliding tests.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, Et=1.14 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa) calibrated from coupon tests. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) validated in separate sliding experiments. Model form judged adequate for the static monotonic loading regime of ASTM F1717."
    },
    {
