      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of production implants. Material properties sourced from certified material test reports for the implant lot. Input uncertainty quantified via ±1 standard deviation sensitivity runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Gradation 3 requires that test samples be production-representative implants with documented lot traceability, and that sample size be sufficient to characterize inter-specimen variability (minimum N=6 per laboratory). N=11 total (6 Lab A, 5 Lab B) from the same production lot satisfies this criterion.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested; all from production lot with full dimensional and material certification. Inter-specimen CV for stiffness <4%, confirming acceptable manufacturing consistency."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
